—ЩSarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/overlay_use.mdЩ@3d94ae9b78a404d57421be54c60cb0f9f4b2621667351719310d17742a0b61c7Іtitle: overlay use‘ЁExamplesЪRCreate an overlay from a module.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    foo


```
Create an overlay from a module and rename it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam as spam_new
    foo


```
Create an overlay with a prefix.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export def foo { "foo" }'
    overlay use --prefix spam
    spam foo


```
Create an overlay from a file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export-env { $env.FOO = "foo" }' | save spam.nu
    overlay use spam.nu
    $env.FOO


```
’ђђЪ„Title: title: overlay use
Path: Examples
Content:
Create an overlay from a module.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    foo


```
Create an overlay from a module and rename it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam as spam_new
    foo


```
Create an overlay with a prefix.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export def foo { "foo" }'
    overlay use --prefix spam
    spam foo


```
Create an overlay from a file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export-env { $env.FOO = "foo" }' | save spam.nu
    overlay use spam.nu
    $env.FOO


```
